WEBVTT

00:00:04.080 --> 00:00:07.560
And this is "ETERNAL Kizuna."

00:00:07.560 --> 00:00:08.560
Congratulations.

00:00:08.560 --> 00:00:10.440
The game we poured our hearts into

00:00:10.440 --> 00:00:11.240
has succeeded

00:00:11.240 --> 00:00:12.800
beyond our expectations.

00:00:13.960 --> 00:00:15.960
I’ll create a character based on me,

00:00:15.960 --> 00:00:17.360
named Haruki.

00:00:17.360 --> 00:00:19.160
Headquarters in Japan

00:00:19.160 --> 00:00:23.160
asked me to return for their big project.

00:00:23.840 --> 00:00:24.280
Phat.

00:00:25.160 --> 00:00:27.200
Not a day went by without thoughts of you.

00:00:28.120 --> 00:00:30.080
Now I know

00:00:30.080 --> 00:00:31.800
how important you are to me.

00:00:58.520 --> 00:00:59.080
Junji.

00:01:01.960 --> 00:01:03.120
You okay, Junji?

00:01:10.160 --> 00:01:10.640
Hey…

00:01:13.600 --> 00:01:14.840
We talked about this.

00:01:15.720 --> 00:01:17.520
When it's time to part ways,

00:01:19.880 --> 00:01:21.040
we wouldn’t cry.

00:01:28.240 --> 00:01:29.400
At first…

00:01:30.040 --> 00:01:31.240
I thought I could do it.

00:01:32.320 --> 00:01:34.280
But…

00:01:34.280 --> 00:01:35.680
Now that it's happening,

00:01:36.640 --> 00:01:37.480
I can't.

00:01:39.280 --> 00:01:42.440
I'm not as strong as you are.

00:01:44.280 --> 00:01:45.120
Don't be like that.

00:01:46.960 --> 00:01:49.800
Don't cry, Jun-chan.

00:01:51.240 --> 00:01:52.640
I promise

00:01:52.640 --> 00:01:53.560
I'll fly over

00:01:53.560 --> 00:01:55.640
to Japan whenever I'm free.

00:01:55.640 --> 00:01:56.360
Okay?

00:01:58.640 --> 00:01:59.920
Thanks, Jeans.

00:02:00.680 --> 00:02:01.360
And…

00:02:01.360 --> 00:02:03.040
Don't worry about Hill, Boss.

00:02:03.520 --> 00:02:04.720
He's in good hands.

00:02:05.160 --> 00:02:07.080
Not a single scratch on him.

00:02:07.240 --> 00:02:09.200
I'll take him out every night

00:02:09.200 --> 00:02:10.600
so he won't ever feel lonely.

00:02:11.160 --> 00:02:11.640
Ouch!

00:02:13.280 --> 00:02:15.360
I was joking. I wouldn't dare.

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:16.560
I think

00:02:16.560 --> 00:02:17.840
you're not crying

00:02:17.840 --> 00:02:19.640
because you'll be far from Hill.

00:02:20.080 --> 00:02:20.720
But because

00:02:20.720 --> 00:02:23.120
you can't eat the green
curry at my place anymore.

00:02:23.120 --> 00:02:23.880
Am I right?

00:02:23.880 --> 00:02:24.920
Really?

00:02:25.520 --> 00:02:26.360
Is that so?

00:02:26.360 --> 00:02:27.840
Maybe.

00:02:30.240 --> 00:02:31.480
Anyway,

00:02:31.480 --> 00:02:32.880
Safe travels, Boss.

00:02:33.960 --> 00:02:35.080
Thanks.

00:02:35.800 --> 00:02:36.960
Don't cry.

00:02:36.960 --> 00:02:37.680
I'm not.

00:02:37.680 --> 00:02:38.600
No more tears.

00:02:39.840 --> 00:02:41.080
Don't cry.

00:02:41.080 --> 00:02:42.520
- I'm not crying.
- Right.

00:02:44.880 --> 00:02:45.440
Let's go.

00:02:46.040 --> 00:02:46.960
Bye-bye.

00:02:55.680 --> 00:02:56.560
I'll help.

00:03:03.200 --> 00:03:05.120
I hope your project goes well.

00:03:06.200 --> 00:03:08.040
I'll always be cheering you on.

00:03:10.000 --> 00:03:11.400
Just like how Yuka

00:03:11.400 --> 00:03:14.000
always supported me with her smile.

00:03:14.880 --> 00:03:16.120
Ganbatte ne!

00:03:19.560 --> 00:03:20.920
Take care of yourself

00:03:21.720 --> 00:03:23.360
while I’m gone.

00:03:27.280 --> 00:03:29.240
Drink lots of water

00:03:29.440 --> 00:03:31.440
when you eat those pork skewers.

00:03:32.160 --> 00:03:32.880
Got it.

00:03:33.400 --> 00:03:34.440
And you too.

00:03:36.440 --> 00:03:38.320
Take care of yourself.

00:03:38.320 --> 00:03:39.800
Get plenty of rest.

00:03:53.200 --> 00:03:54.520
And…

00:03:54.520 --> 00:03:55.880
While I'm here,

00:03:56.680 --> 00:03:58.400
I will…

00:03:58.400 --> 00:04:00.000
make sure I finish Haruki on time.

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:01.600
make sure I finish Haruki on time.

00:04:04.520 --> 00:04:06.520
Promise me

00:04:07.440 --> 00:04:08.640
we’ll say goodbye

00:04:09.960 --> 00:04:11.880
together on Yuka’s last day.

00:04:21.920 --> 00:04:23.640
I promise.

00:05:47.120 --> 00:05:47.800
Junji.

00:05:52.440 --> 00:05:53.120
Junji.

00:06:00.960 --> 00:06:01.800
Hill.

00:06:11.640 --> 00:06:12.480
Junji.

00:07:50.040 --> 00:07:51.960
(Three months later)

00:08:13.280 --> 00:08:15.640
Ohayo (Good morning), Hill.

00:08:18.400 --> 00:08:20.040
Ohayo, Junji.

00:08:20.640 --> 00:08:22.560
You can go back to sleep.

00:08:23.360 --> 00:08:25.160
It’s still early in Thailand.

00:08:25.160 --> 00:08:27.480
You also went to bed late last night.

00:08:29.720 --> 00:08:30.400
No way.

00:08:30.880 --> 00:08:32.320
How could I?

00:08:32.680 --> 00:08:34.920
You're not here with me, Junji.

00:08:35.440 --> 00:08:37.040
Alright, fine.

00:08:37.040 --> 00:08:38.480
Go take a shower.

00:08:38.480 --> 00:08:39.600
Stop talking.

00:08:40.520 --> 00:08:41.400
Right, go shower.

00:08:47.280 --> 00:08:47.960
Hill.

00:08:47.960 --> 00:08:48.800
Hill!

00:08:48.800 --> 00:08:50.040
What are you doing?

00:08:51.720 --> 00:08:53.440
Undress in the bathroom!

00:08:53.440 --> 00:08:55.960
They'll see everything.

00:08:57.480 --> 00:08:58.720
Ta-da!

00:08:58.720 --> 00:08:59.880
Want some?

00:09:00.160 --> 00:09:01.200
Man…

00:09:01.200 --> 00:09:03.640
You're making me want to
go back and have some.

00:09:03.640 --> 00:09:04.920
If you come back today,

00:09:04.920 --> 00:09:06.800
I'll buy you a hundred sticks.

00:09:06.800 --> 00:09:07.240
Here.

00:09:08.720 --> 00:09:10.000
Open wide.

00:09:15.360 --> 00:09:16.760
Get some rest, Hill.

00:09:16.760 --> 00:09:17.640
You could faint.

00:09:17.920 --> 00:09:19.240
But work's not done.

00:09:19.640 --> 00:09:21.000
I want to finish it first.

00:09:22.520 --> 00:09:23.600
I’m so tired, Junji.

00:09:24.400 --> 00:09:26.920
Give me some encouragement.

00:09:26.920 --> 00:09:28.280
No, work until you drop.

00:09:28.280 --> 00:09:29.600
So stubborn.

00:09:30.440 --> 00:09:32.080
Just a bit, please?

00:09:44.080 --> 00:09:45.120
Junji.

00:09:45.120 --> 00:09:48.320
It's so late. You're not afraid of ghosts?

00:09:48.600 --> 00:09:49.280
Boo!

00:09:50.720 --> 00:09:52.040
Ghosts?

00:09:52.040 --> 00:09:53.440
Save that for the kids.

00:09:53.440 --> 00:09:55.680
I just don't want you to stay up late.

00:09:56.040 --> 00:09:57.840
You always work so hard.

00:09:58.800 --> 00:10:00.000
It's been tough lately

00:10:00.000 --> 00:10:00.320
It's been tough lately

00:10:00.320 --> 00:10:01.600
because we just started.

00:10:01.960 --> 00:10:04.560
But I already got a team to help.

00:10:04.560 --> 00:10:06.480
Soon, it’ll be more manageable.

00:10:06.920 --> 00:10:08.720
[sighs]

00:10:08.720 --> 00:10:11.760
I miss green curry and pork skewers a lot.

00:10:16.760 --> 00:10:17.280
So,

00:10:18.160 --> 00:10:19.920
you only miss the food?

00:10:19.920 --> 00:10:21.600
Not anything else?

00:10:22.840 --> 00:10:25.200
Besides food,

00:10:26.120 --> 00:10:27.400
I miss…

00:10:28.640 --> 00:10:29.000
Oh!

00:10:29.640 --> 00:10:30.560
Tourist spots.

00:10:31.600 --> 00:10:34.960
I still have many places in Thailand to visit.

00:10:35.400 --> 00:10:37.280
Chiang Mai is pretty.

00:10:37.280 --> 00:10:38.760
Phuket is also great

00:10:39.800 --> 00:10:41.200
for scuba diving.

00:10:42.320 --> 00:10:46.000
The Full Moon Party in Phang Nga.

00:10:46.400 --> 00:10:47.400
But,

00:10:48.320 --> 00:10:52.280
what I miss the most is…

00:10:58.960 --> 00:10:59.680
Hey.

00:11:00.440 --> 00:11:01.400
You fell asleep?

00:11:07.720 --> 00:11:09.240
You must be

00:11:10.520 --> 00:11:11.720
exhausted as well.

00:11:18.240 --> 00:11:20.000
I just want you

00:11:20.000 --> 00:11:21.280
to take care of yourself.

00:11:22.360 --> 00:11:25.360
Especially when I’m so far away.

00:11:28.960 --> 00:11:30.000
I…

00:11:32.040 --> 00:11:33.280
I miss you, Hill.

00:11:36.600 --> 00:11:37.400
I…

00:11:40.200 --> 00:11:41.240
I really miss you.

00:12:10.080 --> 00:12:13.080
(Babe, what do you want for lunch?)

00:12:18.280 --> 00:12:21.160
(Something hot. How about mala skewers?)

00:12:24.880 --> 00:12:27.480
(Mala may be hot, but not
as hot as me. Tee-hee!)

00:12:35.200 --> 00:12:36.840
Geez.

00:12:36.840 --> 00:12:39.760
You’re only a few steps apart and

00:12:40.000 --> 00:12:41.960
you're still texting each other?

00:12:43.600 --> 00:12:44.720
Alright, everyone.

00:12:44.720 --> 00:12:45.720
Gather around.

00:12:58.400 --> 00:13:00.000
Hello, everyone.

00:13:00.000 --> 00:13:00.280
Hello, everyone.

00:13:01.040 --> 00:13:02.520
- Hello, Boss.
- Hi, Boss.

00:13:02.520 --> 00:13:04.240
Are you well, Ms. Secretary?

00:13:04.800 --> 00:13:06.120
How's the new boss?

00:13:07.400 --> 00:13:10.080
Boss Pao is way stricter than you.

00:13:10.080 --> 00:13:10.920
[laughs]

00:13:11.400 --> 00:13:12.560
Come on, Boss.

00:13:12.560 --> 00:13:13.840
It's only temporary.

00:13:14.280 --> 00:13:16.800
Soon, they'll send someone to replace me.

00:13:17.280 --> 00:13:18.680
That'll take a while.

00:13:18.680 --> 00:13:21.320
They won't find someone that quickly.

00:13:22.920 --> 00:13:26.320
And you seem like a good fit for the role.

00:13:27.280 --> 00:13:28.320
You mean it?

00:13:28.320 --> 00:13:29.800
Don't flatter me.

00:13:30.960 --> 00:13:31.520
Anyway,

00:13:31.520 --> 00:13:33.680
I'll boot up the PC for your remote access.

00:13:34.200 --> 00:13:37.280
I've shared the livestream
schedule prep with the fans,

00:13:37.280 --> 00:13:39.200
through PRISMSTAR TH Channel Online,

00:13:39.200 --> 00:13:41.040
as you've requested.

00:13:41.040 --> 00:13:42.040
Under the topic of

00:13:42.040 --> 00:13:44.320
online game development in Japan.

00:13:45.160 --> 00:13:47.760
Thank you, everyone.

00:13:52.640 --> 00:13:53.560
Alright.

00:13:53.560 --> 00:13:54.600
Back to work.

00:13:54.600 --> 00:13:55.080
Go on.

00:14:00.400 --> 00:14:01.760
I saw that, dear.

00:14:10.240 --> 00:14:12.400
Aren't you going back to work?

00:14:15.280 --> 00:14:17.600
I'm just looking ahead, to where…

00:14:17.600 --> 00:14:19.280
our company's future is.

00:14:20.720 --> 00:14:21.800
I'm not at the office.

00:14:21.800 --> 00:14:22.680
I'm at Phat's place.

00:14:23.160 --> 00:14:23.960
What's up, Hill?

00:14:24.640 --> 00:14:26.560
I haven't seen you in days, bro.

00:14:26.560 --> 00:14:28.600
Thought you'd quit and become a chef.

00:14:29.200 --> 00:14:30.160
You little…

00:14:30.160 --> 00:14:32.040
Now you're teasing me.

00:14:32.280 --> 00:14:33.760
I'm here because of

00:14:33.760 --> 00:14:34.880
the new project.

00:14:35.160 --> 00:14:37.640
It's a restaurant simulation game.

00:14:37.640 --> 00:14:39.680
So, I have to do my research here.

00:14:40.000 --> 00:14:42.640
And how's that coming along?

00:14:42.640 --> 00:14:43.920
Still in the research stage.

00:14:44.320 --> 00:14:45.920
That's dope.

00:14:46.400 --> 00:14:47.800
Is it the data you sent me?

00:14:48.040 --> 00:14:51.160
All those restaurant ingredients looked amazing.

00:14:51.160 --> 00:14:52.960
I think you should add

00:14:52.960 --> 00:14:54.200
150 more vegetables.

00:14:55.160 --> 00:14:56.960
Dylon works at a Japanese restaurant.

00:14:56.960 --> 00:14:58.160
Stop messing around, dude.

00:14:58.720 --> 00:14:59.160
Ugh.

00:15:07.400 --> 00:15:07.960
Ready?

00:15:08.320 --> 00:15:09.760
Hang on, let me get the gloves.

00:15:13.880 --> 00:15:15.080
These are such a pain.

00:15:16.000 --> 00:15:16.680
Ah…

00:15:16.680 --> 00:15:17.080
Here.

00:15:17.080 --> 00:15:17.400
Pull.

00:15:18.240 --> 00:15:19.360
Okay, all set.

00:15:20.600 --> 00:15:22.080
Before we make sashimi,

00:15:22.080 --> 00:15:23.560
we need to slice the fish first.

00:15:23.880 --> 00:15:25.120
Ready, Chef Bay?

00:15:25.360 --> 00:15:26.320
Ready, Chef Phat.

00:15:26.600 --> 00:15:27.120
Mwah, mwah.

00:15:27.480 --> 00:15:28.720
Quit fooling around.

00:15:28.720 --> 00:15:29.360
Focus.

00:15:30.000 --> 00:15:31.240
Here, start slicing.

00:15:31.960 --> 00:15:32.920
How?

00:15:32.920 --> 00:15:34.600
I literally just showed you.

00:15:34.800 --> 00:15:35.240
Right.

00:15:35.720 --> 00:15:36.560
More diagonally.

00:15:37.160 --> 00:15:38.760
- That's good.
- Like this?

00:15:38.760 --> 00:15:40.040
Too thick.

00:15:40.040 --> 00:15:41.360
What? Still too thick?

00:15:42.560 --> 00:15:43.400
Seriously.

00:15:44.440 --> 00:15:45.360
Okay.

00:15:45.360 --> 00:15:46.400
Good.

00:15:46.720 --> 00:15:47.160
Ow!

00:15:47.320 --> 00:15:48.720
Did you cut yourself?

00:15:49.680 --> 00:15:50.240
Maybe.

00:15:50.240 --> 00:15:50.720
Ouch!

00:15:51.200 --> 00:15:52.480
Stop messing about.

00:15:52.680 --> 00:15:52.920
Come on.

00:15:52.920 --> 00:15:53.720
Focus.

00:15:54.000 --> 00:15:55.400
A little encouragement?

00:15:55.760 --> 00:15:57.200
Just hurry up.

00:15:57.200 --> 00:15:59.320
I got it. I'm done!

00:15:59.320 --> 00:16:00.000
See?

00:16:00.000 --> 00:16:00.280
See?

00:16:01.480 --> 00:16:02.120
There.

00:16:02.120 --> 00:16:03.800
It's finished. Where's my praise?

00:16:06.560 --> 00:16:07.080
Good.

00:16:07.440 --> 00:16:08.400
Do I get a reward?

00:16:08.720 --> 00:16:09.600
What reward?

00:16:10.040 --> 00:16:11.280
But we're packed today.

00:16:12.520 --> 00:16:14.360
It's fine, we just need to adjust a bit.

00:16:16.080 --> 00:16:16.640
Quick.

00:16:19.760 --> 00:16:20.440
That's it.

00:16:21.360 --> 00:16:22.800
The camera's rolling, you know?

00:16:23.880 --> 00:16:24.960
Careful.

00:16:24.960 --> 00:16:27.000
You’ll knock over the glasses.

00:16:27.440 --> 00:16:28.400
Oh, man.

00:16:30.240 --> 00:16:31.040
Ta-da!

00:16:31.040 --> 00:16:32.240
Perfectly done.

00:16:32.240 --> 00:16:33.840
Well? Check it out.

00:16:34.320 --> 00:16:35.520
How is this perfect?

00:16:35.840 --> 00:16:37.160
It’s wrong.

00:16:37.160 --> 00:16:38.200
But I did as you said.

00:16:38.200 --> 00:16:39.160
I copied yours.

00:16:39.160 --> 00:16:40.880
No, that's not right.

00:16:41.160 --> 00:16:41.840
Sitting here,

00:16:41.840 --> 00:16:42.480
the placement

00:16:42.480 --> 00:16:43.960
is in this order, right?

00:16:43.960 --> 00:16:45.120
For this side…

00:16:45.120 --> 00:16:46.960
you have to arrange in the same order.

00:16:47.160 --> 00:16:48.080
Spoon's of the left.

00:16:48.080 --> 00:16:49.480
But you put it on the right.

00:16:49.480 --> 00:16:50.320
They're a lefty.

00:16:50.320 --> 00:16:51.320
No.

00:16:51.320 --> 00:16:51.840
See?

00:16:51.840 --> 00:16:54.040
You talk back every single time.

00:17:02.400 --> 00:17:03.440
Sorry.

00:17:03.840 --> 00:17:04.680
But,

00:17:04.680 --> 00:17:06.040
there's no need to shout.

00:17:06.040 --> 00:17:07.840
You're the reason I had to.

00:17:07.840 --> 00:17:08.160
Come on.

00:17:09.200 --> 00:17:09.800
Hurry up.

00:17:11.120 --> 00:17:12.320
Switch them.

00:17:12.720 --> 00:17:14.120
Softer, will you?

00:17:18.480 --> 00:17:19.920
That’s not right.

00:17:19.920 --> 00:17:22.000
The knife should go on the inside.

00:17:22.400 --> 00:17:23.720
Ugh.

00:17:23.720 --> 00:17:24.800
Why so difficult?

00:17:24.800 --> 00:17:25.680
It’s all cutlery.

00:17:25.920 --> 00:17:28.360
Make sure the wine glass
is at an angle.

00:17:28.360 --> 00:17:29.120
That'll make it easier to grab it.

00:17:29.120 --> 00:17:29.800
- That'll make it easier to grab it.
- Wait.

00:17:29.800 --> 00:17:30.760
Forty five degrees?

00:17:31.560 --> 00:17:32.520
Yes, here.

00:17:32.520 --> 00:17:33.520
You tricked me again.

00:17:33.520 --> 00:17:34.560
Do it yourself.

00:17:35.080 --> 00:17:35.560
Ugh.

00:17:35.560 --> 00:17:37.000
- Like this? Good?
- Yeah.

00:17:37.000 --> 00:17:37.680
That's right.

00:17:38.080 --> 00:17:39.040
- Finally.
- Good.

00:17:39.040 --> 00:17:39.760
What’s next?

00:17:40.360 --> 00:17:41.640
Where’s the napkin?

00:17:42.040 --> 00:17:42.680
Huh?

00:17:42.680 --> 00:17:43.680
I told you already.

00:17:43.680 --> 00:17:44.400
Where is it?

00:17:44.400 --> 00:17:46.160
I don't know. How could I know?

00:17:46.160 --> 00:17:48.640
I sent you a list of things to prepare.

00:17:48.760 --> 00:17:50.000
- But it’s your place.
- Go.

00:17:50.000 --> 00:17:50.800
Doesn't matter.

00:17:59.920 --> 00:18:00.000
Which hair color

00:18:00.000 --> 00:18:02.000
Which hair color

00:18:02.000 --> 00:18:03.720
would suit Haruki?

00:18:03.720 --> 00:18:05.280
I'd say gray.

00:18:05.280 --> 00:18:06.360
Or silver.

00:18:06.360 --> 00:18:09.080
It's a nice contrast to Yuka's pink hair.

00:18:09.600 --> 00:18:10.440
Okay, let's see.

00:18:10.440 --> 00:18:11.080
Let's go.

00:18:12.960 --> 00:18:14.160
[background chatter] Gray, like this.

00:18:14.160 --> 00:18:14.920
[background chatter] Yeah.

