Feeling lonely?

00:35:34.040 --> 00:35:36.240
Let me be your friend.

00:35:38.600 --> 00:35:39.480
Ganbatte ne!

00:35:39.680 --> 00:35:40.960
You can do it!

00:35:40.960 --> 00:35:42.960
I'm waiting for the day you succeed.

00:35:43.440 --> 00:35:44.560
Ganbatte ne!

00:35:44.800 --> 00:35:46.040
Rise and shine.

00:35:46.040 --> 00:35:47.160
It's time to wake up.

00:35:58.880 --> 00:36:00.000
Yeah!

00:36:00.000 --> 00:36:00.320
Yeah!

00:36:02.960 --> 00:36:04.800
Yuka.

00:36:04.800 --> 00:36:06.120
I completed the mission.

00:36:06.120 --> 00:36:06.920
Yuka!

00:36:06.920 --> 00:36:08.240
It'll be fine, Hill.

00:36:08.240 --> 00:36:09.440
I know you can do it.

00:36:10.240 --> 00:36:11.040
Thanks, Yuka.

00:36:11.840 --> 00:36:14.200
I won’t let you disappear.

00:37:11.440 --> 00:37:13.920
(I'm heading to the airport now.)

00:38:53.160 --> 00:38:55.600
I went all the way to Japan to see you.

00:38:56.160 --> 00:38:57.360
What the hell, Junji.

00:38:58.240 --> 00:38:59.560
What got you so busy?

00:39:13.320 --> 00:39:13.800
Look.

00:39:14.360 --> 00:39:16.000
These nice gifts.

00:39:17.600 --> 00:39:19.040
But you don’t get them, Junji.

00:39:19.040 --> 00:39:19.840
Serves you right.

00:39:21.120 --> 00:39:22.120
[doorbell rings]

00:39:25.240 --> 00:39:26.240
[doorbell rings]

00:39:28.520 --> 00:39:28.920
[doorbell rings]

00:39:28.920 --> 00:39:30.440
I'm coming.

00:39:30.440 --> 00:39:31.920
Once is enough.

00:39:32.480 --> 00:39:33.680
[doorbell rings]

00:40:08.280 --> 00:40:09.080
Junji.

00:40:11.320 --> 00:40:12.360
Did you miss me,

00:40:13.160 --> 00:40:13.640
Hill?

00:40:46.120 --> 00:40:46.800
Hold up.

00:40:46.800 --> 00:40:47.080
Why?

00:40:47.600 --> 00:40:48.760
Don’t hug me.

00:40:49.440 --> 00:40:50.800
You broke your promise.

00:40:52.520 --> 00:40:54.080
You promised

00:40:54.080 --> 00:40:56.320
to be with me on Yuka’s last day.

00:40:57.000 --> 00:40:58.120
But you didn’t.

00:40:58.760 --> 00:41:00.000
I went all the way to Japan.

00:41:00.000 --> 00:41:00.600
I went all the way to Japan.

00:41:01.040 --> 00:41:02.440
Even if we couldn’t meet up,

00:41:03.120 --> 00:41:04.200
we could've called.

00:41:04.200 --> 00:41:05.400
Or read my messages.

00:41:07.360 --> 00:41:08.880
I know you're sulking.

00:41:09.800 --> 00:41:10.800
I'm sorry.

00:41:12.000 --> 00:41:12.720
But…

00:41:13.600 --> 00:41:14.920
Work was really tough.

00:41:15.480 --> 00:41:20.320
You must be really, really busy.

00:41:21.240 --> 00:41:22.680
It was urgent.

00:41:22.680 --> 00:41:26.800
Had to fly to Korea for
a big sponsorship deal.

00:41:27.880 --> 00:41:30.280
I was on the plane

00:41:30.280 --> 00:41:31.240
when you called.

00:41:32.520 --> 00:41:34.480
After I'm done, I rushed to see you.

00:41:34.480 --> 00:41:36.360
So I did as I promised.

00:41:39.840 --> 00:41:41.400
Yeah, yeah.

00:41:41.400 --> 00:41:43.200
Have you eaten?

00:41:43.200 --> 00:41:45.600
I came straight to you.

00:41:45.600 --> 00:41:46.760
So…

00:41:46.760 --> 00:41:48.360
I haven't eaten anything.

00:41:49.800 --> 00:41:50.760
You can have this.

00:41:50.760 --> 00:41:51.880
It's your gift.

00:41:56.120 --> 00:41:56.560
What?

00:41:57.400 --> 00:41:59.080
Go shower first.

00:41:59.080 --> 00:41:59.640
Ugh.

00:41:59.640 --> 00:42:00.000
You just got back.

00:42:00.000 --> 00:42:01.000
You just got back.

00:42:01.000 --> 00:42:02.480
Go, go.

00:42:02.480 --> 00:42:03.960
Alright, mom.

00:42:05.360 --> 00:42:06.320
Together?

00:42:06.320 --> 00:42:06.920
Hey!

00:42:07.640 --> 00:42:08.680
Fine, come on.

00:42:11.760 --> 00:42:12.880
Junji.

00:42:12.880 --> 00:42:13.920
How is it?

00:42:13.920 --> 00:42:14.960
Tastes good?

00:42:15.560 --> 00:42:16.920
Good.

00:42:19.120 --> 00:42:19.840
Tomorrow,

00:42:20.240 --> 00:42:23.080
I'll take you out for some good food.

00:42:25.000 --> 00:42:26.960
How long are you staying for?

00:42:29.480 --> 00:42:30.560
Three days.

00:42:33.560 --> 00:42:34.480
Only three days?

00:42:35.200 --> 00:42:36.160
That's so short.

00:42:36.920 --> 00:42:38.600
Thought you'd be here longer.

00:42:40.200 --> 00:42:41.520
Just a brief visit, huh?

00:42:42.880 --> 00:42:43.920
It's alright.

00:42:44.800 --> 00:42:46.560
Better than not seeing you at all.

00:42:48.400 --> 00:42:49.800
The thing is,

00:42:49.800 --> 00:42:51.360
I've been counting days

00:42:51.360 --> 00:42:53.480
until your project is over.

00:42:54.120 --> 00:42:55.560
So we can be together again.

00:43:20.000 --> 00:43:20.640
Junji.

00:43:22.480 --> 00:43:23.640
Are you okay?

00:43:28.120 --> 00:43:28.840
Junji.

00:43:28.840 --> 00:43:30.200
If I

00:43:30.200 --> 00:43:32.160
ever make you uncomfortable,

00:43:33.440 --> 00:43:34.240
just tell me.

00:43:35.320 --> 00:43:36.360
It’s better than

00:43:38.280 --> 00:43:40.640
seeing you suffer like this.

00:43:45.840 --> 00:43:46.880
I…

00:43:52.640 --> 00:43:54.200
I have something important

00:43:55.360 --> 00:43:56.600
to tell you, Hill.

00:43:57.600 --> 00:43:58.480
But…

00:44:02.080 --> 00:44:03.960
What is it, Junji?

00:44:05.760 --> 00:44:06.720
You can tell me.

00:44:10.480 --> 00:44:11.200
I…

00:44:11.880 --> 00:44:14.200
I don’t think I’ll be
coming back to Thailand.

00:44:17.440 --> 00:44:20.560
Jeans will also relocate to Japan.

00:44:22.280 --> 00:44:23.840
To find new inspiration.

00:44:28.600 --> 00:44:30.880
When I said I might not be back,

00:44:32.000 --> 00:44:33.120
it's because this project

00:44:35.720 --> 00:44:36.960
is really big.

00:44:38.120 --> 00:44:39.880
Two years, at least.

00:44:44.400 --> 00:44:45.120
Junji.

00:44:48.080 --> 00:44:51.320
So we really won't get to be together?

00:44:56.200 --> 00:44:58.680
If that's the case…

00:45:03.600 --> 00:45:05.600
Can I ask you for one thing?

00:45:41.800 --> 00:45:42.720
Junji.

00:46:00.560 --> 00:46:01.280
Hill.

00:46:03.760 --> 00:46:04.840
In Japan,

00:46:05.640 --> 00:46:07.840
they're looking for a skilled Game Designer

00:46:08.840 --> 00:46:09.960
for the project.

00:46:11.280 --> 00:46:12.720
I was asked to

00:46:14.640 --> 00:46:15.920
invite you

00:46:17.480 --> 00:46:18.760
to come work in Japan.

00:46:20.760 --> 00:46:23.680
You've only worked here for a year,

00:46:23.680 --> 00:46:25.000
but

00:46:25.000 --> 00:46:27.280
your work is amazing.

00:46:27.920 --> 00:46:30.000
Everyone recognized your work.

00:46:35.240 --> 00:46:36.160
Junji.

00:46:39.800 --> 00:46:41.000
I'm happy

00:46:41.000 --> 00:46:42.480
about work,

00:46:42.480 --> 00:46:42.800
but

00:46:45.040 --> 00:46:46.720
what makes me happiest

00:46:46.720 --> 00:46:48.440
is the fact that I'll get to

00:46:48.920 --> 00:46:50.480
hug you in person.

00:46:50.480 --> 00:46:53.000
No more sending you hugs through the phone.

00:46:55.240 --> 00:46:56.560
You really mean it?

00:46:56.560 --> 00:46:57.440
Yeah.

00:46:58.360 --> 00:46:59.560
- Really?
- Really.

00:46:59.560 --> 00:47:00.000
Don't cry.

00:47:00.000 --> 00:47:00.160
Don't cry.

00:47:31.960 --> 00:47:33.080
Junji.

00:47:33.080 --> 00:47:34.160
You're late.

00:47:34.160 --> 00:47:34.960
Sorry.

00:47:37.560 --> 00:47:38.480
Shall we go?

00:48:02.800 --> 00:48:03.840
Junji-san.

00:48:04.680 --> 00:48:05.800
Will you be my boyfriend?

00:48:06.280 --> 00:48:07.480
Thank you for

00:48:07.480 --> 00:48:09.040
always

00:48:09.040 --> 00:48:10.080
supporting me.

00:48:10.400 --> 00:48:11.440
I love you.

00:48:17.480 --> 00:48:18.760
Without Yuka,

00:48:19.160 --> 00:48:20.880
I wouldn’t be who I am today.

00:48:21.200 --> 00:48:22.320
But really,

00:48:22.840 --> 00:48:24.320
I should be thanking you.

00:48:31.120 --> 00:48:32.240
Forget the past.

00:48:32.240 --> 00:48:35.160
Let's make new memories together.

00:49:05.920 --> 00:49:14.120
(At the company party)

00:49:52.440 --> 00:49:55.200
Let me introduce our
new Senior Game Designer

00:49:55.200 --> 00:49:56.320
from Thailand.

00:49:56.920 --> 00:49:57.240
Please.

00:50:02.720 --> 00:50:03.480
Hello.

00:50:04.240 --> 00:50:04.920
I'm Hill.

00:50:05.280 --> 00:50:07.600
Nice to meet you all.

00:50:28.560 --> 00:50:30.640
Just messing with you.

00:50:42.240 --> 00:50:43.000
Have a seat.

00:50:46.560 --> 00:50:47.120
This is Hill.

00:50:47.120 --> 00:50:48.240
Ah, Mr. Hill.

00:50:48.240 --> 00:50:49.360
Nice to meet you, Hill.

00:50:51.440 --> 00:50:52.160
Nice to meet you.

00:51:00.240 --> 00:51:01.920
Can you speak Japanese?

00:51:02.600 --> 00:51:03.640
A little bit.

00:51:05.920 --> 00:51:07.400
I'm Japanese.